cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with extracting shape information from images using shading. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to infer local shape distributions, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of local shape distributions to reconstruct object-scale shape could also place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper's focus on efficient and robust reconstruction of shape could also place it in the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of a quadratic representation of local shape could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
